Bug.WithStack:
New build box having out of memory or possibly file i/o issues running JDK 1.4.2 32-bit on 64-bit OS (Debian Sarge kernel 2.6). This bug is a placeholder for CVS commits (memory tuning) and to dump gotchas or discovered solutions, in case other teams plan to migrate to a 64-bit OS as their build infrastructure, but also plan to support 32-bit JDKs.
As 64-bit builds are not supported (reference platform) yet, this is only a minor bug, since we can always revert to our previous OS configuration if needs be. Further discussion on this topic suggests that it might be the dual-processor nature of the machine, not the 32bit-in-64bit issue. I noticed that this in SDOUtilProtectedGetTest can fail
assertEquals(new Date(), TypeConverter.getDate(new Date()));
because it can construct two different dates if System.currentTimeMillis happens to change between the two calls. This should avoid that issue:
Date date = new Date(); assertEquals(date, TypeConverter.getDate(date));
Fixed in 2.2.0 I200511291121 Move to verified as per bug 206558.

